<p class=""><h2>Key Challenges in the CBRN Air Filtration System Market</h2><ul>    <li><strong>Technological Complexity:</strong> The development of CBRN air filtration systems requires sophisticated technology and innovation. Companies often face challenges in integrating advanced materials and mechanisms that effectively neutralize chemical, biological, radiological, and nuclear threats.</li>    <li><strong>Regulatory Compliances:</strong> Manufacturers must navigate a complex landscape of regulations and standards set by various safety and health organizations. Compliance can be time-consuming and costly, often leading to delays in product development and market entry.</li>    <li><strong>High Costs:</strong> The investment needed for the research and development of CBRN filtration systems can be substantial. This high cost can be a barrier for smaller companies, limiting competition and innovation in the market.</li>    <li><strong>Market Awareness:</strong> There is often a lack of awareness and understanding among potential end-users regarding the importance of CBRN air filtration systems. This may hinder demand and the overall growth of the market.</li>    <li><strong>Infrastructure Limitations:</strong> Inadequate infrastructure for deploying advanced air filtration systems, especially in developing regions, poses a challenge. Many systems require significant installation and maintenance resources that are not readily available.</li></ul><h2>Potential Growth Opportunities in the CBRN Air Filtration System Market</h2><ul>    <li><strong>Increased Demand from Healthcare Sector:</strong> Heightened awareness regarding airborne pathogens due to global health crises has elevated the demand for efficient filtration systems in hospitals and healthcare facilities, creating significant market opportunities.</li>    <li><strong>Advancements in Materials Science:</strong> Innovations in nanotechnology and materials science can lead to the development of more effective